*To configure git :

git config --global user.email "xx@xx"
git config --global user.name "YYY"
git config --global color.ui true

---------

*Display the config values :

git config --list 

---------

*To initialize a git repository (fo rm within a directory) :

git init 

---------

Staging = a type of transition zone, by which entries will be marked as tracked/staged/considered for 		  the next commit ... etc

*To Add/stage a file :

git add <file_name> 

---------

*Save/commit changes :

1- git commit 
2- Entre commit message

OR 

1- git commit -m "commit_message_xx"

---------

*Disply the status of the git repository :
git status

---------

*Stage file(s) and Commit at once : 
git commit -a -m "commit_message_xx"

---------

*Add/track file(s) :
git add <file>

---------

*Add/track file(s) of a given type :
git add *.<extension_name>

---------

*Add/track all files :
git add --all

---------

*Ignore file(s) or directories : mention them in .gitignore

---------

*To list history of commits :

git log -n <number_of_commits>

---------

*To list history of commits in a user-friendly formats, one line/decorated ...etc :

git log -n <number_of_commits> --oneline
 
git log -n <number_of_commits> --decorate

---------

*To list history of commits that affected a given file or directory :

git log -n <number_of_commits> -p <file_or_directory_name>

---------

* To display the changes made on the repository since the last commit :

git diff  





  









